      • uk.ac.ed.epcc.webapp.preferences.AbstractUserSettingFactory<D,T,S>
  • Type Parameters:
    D - Type of the setting value
    T - Database persistance type
    S - Type of Setting object
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Contexed, ContextCached, FormCreatorProducer, FormUpdateProducer<S>, FilterMatcher<S>, TypeConverter<S,java.lang.Number>, DataObjectSelector<S>, Selector<DataObjectItemInput<S>>, Owner<S>, IndexedProducer<S>, Tagged, Targetted<S>

    public abstract class AbstractUserSettingFactory<D,T,S extends AbstractUserSettingFactory.UserSetting<D>>
extends DataObjectFactory<S>
    An abstract class to hold user Preference settings. This can be sub-classed to store settings with different datatypes.

      • getTarget

        public java.lang.Class<S> getTarget()
        Description copied from class: DataObjectFactory
        Get a bound on the type of object produced by this factory for run-time checking. This implements IndexedProducer.getTarget(). Normally this method should be overridden each time we make a sub-class that narrows the produced type. However checks should still pass if the super-type method is retained.
